<br>
Off topic: Stop being so greedy yourself. Likely you're in a guild so you should be helping to keep your guild clerics supplied with dots. Many selfless players carry stacks to give to their guild clerics. Noone likes to group with a punk who's immediately start crying about giving up a pearl necklace.<br>
<br>
'MINE MINE MINE' is a good way to not get grouped in the future.<br>
<br>
On topic: Depending on your level, Gornit in OOT is a 6 minute spawn and there's a chance that he drops gems. I believe he's exp until the high 40s, and the seafury's are exp and gem droppers until the early-mid 50s. My wizard soloed Gornit for hours and never left with empty pockets.<br>
<br>
Also, if you have a partner or small group, do the mushrooms in FG. Their stalks can sell nicely with Pristine's worth 8 plat I believe at the most. Oh, and the bugs in FG drop nice sellable loot as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uewanakanach0king.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ewan aka nach0king</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 9:21:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11669.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advise on some cash flow increases</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> OFF TOPIC:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Almost every 60cleric I run into has a 100k+ horse, so ya stfu and no I dont give them gems, cost of reagents is class related just as dying is part of my class risk. If anyone would care to trade a death every hour for a peridot im game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My girlfriend, who plays a 56 Cleric, has a 120k horse and 40k banked. I assure you, this money did not come from hoarding excess fire opals in Sebilis. Rather, from her 205 jewelry and 225 tinkering skills, and devotion to farming components and making armour for the open market. Remember, just as many Clerics can be good trainers as any other class. I don't doubt some Clerics do ride the gem gravy train, but don't tar them all with the same brush <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> On Topic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Hunt in places with a good gem count, e.g. B2 in Sebilis with a trio of people for a few hours. Rogue, Monk and Shaman is a brilliant combo. You'll get dozens and dozens of gems, including Blue Diamonds.<br>
<br>
If Iksar Jail is uncamped, sneak down there and you'll make at least 100pp from stealing from the four Iksar there.<br>
<br>
Head all over Sebilis stealing. It truly is a haven for thieves if you're fast with your Hide button.<br>
<br>
Cazic-Thule is a good idea to getcha EXP on. Pretty much all the loot is worth at least 5k. The Tae Ew War Maul and Prelate's Lantern aren't worth nearly as much due to their ready availability. The Earrings from Planks are great to wear; basically you'll not be able to buy a better upgrade in your situation, so you may as well keep them. Anyway, CT gravy loot is a great money-spinner.<br>
<br>
Bazaar. Buy low, sell high. It's REALLY hard these days unless you have a great deal of starting capital (most sub-10k items are crashing in value, on BB at least) but if you have patience go for it. Of course, just going AFK with all the accumulated trash is a good way to earn a little.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Slighty Off-Topic:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If you don't wanna spend too much on gear, look into the possibility of getting into east/west ToV raids. I don't know about your server, but on Bristlebane it's fairly easy to get into one of the many public HoT raids, and if you persevere you can get a great suit of armour. (The loot rules are usually quite harsh on 'casual' raiders; you'll need to undergo several raids before you complete a set.)<br>
<br>
Jokah<br>
Gnome<br>
