<br>
Tradeskills are cash cows these days, but unless you have a good idea of who is doing want on your server, and what they are short on, it is somewhat hard to do. A good cash cow if you dont mind clicking, is making celestrial essence and selling it in the bazaar. You can also get some smithing skill, and collect velium when you hunt velks anyway. You can turn the bricks into small pieces, rings or folded sheets, depending on demand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usilvorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 3:58:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11669.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advise on some cash flow increases</span><hr size=1> My solution to a cleric that takes EVERY gem drop? I dust off my pick pocket key. <br>
<br>
But on the cash making note. I can knock down pretty good cash on ogre guards. Go inside Ogguk and mow em down. There's a merchant right there to sell to. Every guard has a weapon, maybe a crude stein, and a shield. Some have 2 weapons and they aren't hard to solo at 55 plus with decent gear. Bring a bow and arrow for pulling. And they are never camped. Other option would be solb/sola the FS and herb drops add up. Yes I go for the more out of the way spots.You canl make more there than waiting hours to get the gornit camp or fighting for every HG with the 30 other people trying to make cash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhandorphist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HandorPhist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 8:06:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11669.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advise on some cash flow increases</span><hr size=1> Back when FBSS's were still going for 10k pp (pre-Kunark, pre-PNP) my regular play group on my first server gave up after three nights in a row of trying for Frenzy room.  So we went to Oggok.  All mid/upper 40s -- Ranger, Monk, Bard, Chanter, Cleric, usually a Rogue.  Chanter did nothing but buff, loot, and sell -- didn't have time to do anything else!  The cleric made a newb Ogre to hold all coin when the chanter got encumbered and we'd have him bank at the end of each night (we kept all coin except for copper).  We made over 20k in three sessions (between three and four hours each time) clearing the ogre spawns -- and got some experience to boot.  And after three nights bought two FBSS's.  <br>
<br>
Of course they don't spawn as quickly now so you won't see the same results -- but it's still worth the effort.  There is one roamer that comes all the way to the merchant by the zone -- if you grab him first you'll avoid some unpleasantness.  There are other roamers but they come no closer than the citadel or caves so if you are careful you can single pull back towards the zone and have plenty of room to kill.  Sell to the merchant right at the zone -- and sell your steins, they add up over time and you'll always get more.  (Plus you avoid newb beggers lurking to vulture the corpses)<br>
<br>
If you're careful you can bank in Oggok, too -- there is only the one guard to watch for when your hide goes.  Or if you have a friend or second account do like we did, and use an Ogre newb warrior (150 str can carry a ton of coin).<br>
<br>
One thing to be aware of -- they are highly magic resistant.  Won't affect rogues, but will impact any friends you bring along. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevtheif.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KevTheif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 9:57:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11669.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> yar if your looking for cash and exp go to seb. and bind or put a twink in bazaar to find good deals every now and then hehe.<br>
